         ---<BR>Ok, sure...<BR>But show me a static always-spawned low level mob that never dies.<BR>---</P><P>Could say cursed traveller, but I think they changed him too. Doesn't matter though, if a such mobs produce incorrect parsing results (and in this way causing people to get the wrong idea about the different type of classes), they shouldn't be in game. If the results from the parsing were correct, the same results would show when log parsing using standard killable mobs.</P><P>---<BR>Well you don't have to be an ass about it..<BR>Fact of the matter is, VI has screwed us just as much as helped.<BR>---</P><P>Sorry, didn't mean to be rude, I'm just by annoyed those few people whining and complaining about completely legitimate changes to the game. </P><P>VI hasn't "screwed" us. VI change the game as time goes, in order to balance it and make it fun for the majority of players to play. Why? Because that's how they make money. We pay if we think it's fun to play. Therefore, VI try to make it fun to play. This includes both "n.erfing" and strengthening classes in order to obtain balance. </P><P>---<BR>They made things easy by giving all of us (my main is a WAR) melees a static, low level/ac mob that we can attack FOREVER. This made things easy on us and allowed for some new observations to be made...obviously not to VI's liking.<BR>The purpose of the Soulbinders, as stated by Dirth Darkseeder is "we put them in to help out people who were waiting unreasonable amounts of time to find someone to bind them. We didn't put them in for people to attack in the middle of towns as a testing dummy that didn’t fight back or call for help." Obviously they didn't want people having a test dummy, but big deal, give us a break.<BR>---</P><P>If people draw erronous conclusions on rather important things like melee dps, based on a parse from a non-standard mob, what would you do? I think the original post had a great point, which is: "if we didn't want you to be able to parse damage effectively, we'd just stop logging damage in your log files instead of removing the ability to fight defenseless soul binders".</P><P>I don't think VI cares if we're able to test dmg output for different classes. Their intention by removing our ability to fight soulbinders was NOT to take away a testing dummy, it was to make sure we didn't make incorrect assumptions based on log parses which are incorrect, due to the nature of this mob.</P><P>VI is not an evil conspired company, they're here for US, not because they're nice, but because we pay to play the game. Simple as that.</P><P>---<BR>When people get mad at VI, it's because of personal misfortune...they are not trying to ruin your gaming experience..that only happens if YOU LET THEM.<BR>---</P><P>Correct, because of personal misfortune AND inability to see the greater perspective. Verant is not trying to ruin anyones game experience, not even if you let them, they are trying to make the game fun, challening and evolving, to add players to their playerbase, and to keep the ones that exist. I think it's great Verant listens to players about things like the pet haste bug, they do this because it's in their interest to keep people happy, and playing the game.</P><P>Ghoulia Ghostbuster,<BR>Untwinked ghetto defiler of the 55th season,<BR>Kane Bayle</P><P>My ghetto gear: <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=322262" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=322262</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
